## Mechanism
Per-type Timeout (default 10m, 0=unlimited) wraps ctx with context.WithTimeout before exec.CommandContext; ctx-taxonomy refined to "timed out after <dur>: %w(ctx.Err())" (preserves errors.Is). cmd.WaitDelay (var, default 10s) set before Run bounds cmd.Wait against an inherited-pipe hang. MaxOutputBytes (default 64 MiB) hard cap via LimitReader after the existing regular-file Lstat. Defaults applied at the 4 CLI constructors (replay resolveRunner, bench resolveRunner+resolveJudge, retro NewExecGenerator); zero-value structs stay unlimited (backward compatible).

